main event: A bright green object was observed approaching an aircraft at a high rate of speed over the Pacific Ocean on September 27, 1952.
interesting points: The object appeared to be about 5 feet in diameter and was observed for approximately 30-40 seconds before disappearing into a cloud bank.
The location of the sighting coincided with the location of a Soviet mid-Pacific impact area, but the time of the sighting was outside of the announced times for the Soviet tests.
The object was described as descending rapidly, then slowing down and appearing to float like a parachute.
No discernible features, tail trails, exhaust, or sound were reported.
The observer was a pilot, and the sighting occurred while the aircraft was at an altitude of 25,000 feet.
